<main>
    <article class="article-content">
        <div class="article-header">
            <span class="category-tag">Basketball</span>
            <h1>LeBron Leads Lakers to Thrilling Overtime Victory Against Warriors</h1>
            <div class="article-meta">
                <span>By Michael Johnson</span>
                <span>April 20, 2025</span>
                <span>6 min read</span>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="article-image">
            <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1581578016318-df9ef4fcf1bb?q=80&w=2070" alt="Lakers vs Warriors game">
            <p class="image-caption">LeBron James celebrates after hitting the game-winning shot in overtime.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="article-body">
            <p class="lead">In a nail-biting matchup at the Crypto.com Arena, the Los Angeles Lakers secured a dramatic overtime victory against the Golden State Warriors, with LeBron James leading the charge with 38 points.</p>

            <h2>A Battle of Titans</h2>
            <p>Both teams traded leads throughout the game, showcasing elite defense and highlight-reel plays. Stephen Curry dazzled with 33 points, including 7 three-pointers, while Anthony Davis added 22 points and 15 rebounds for the Lakers.</p>

            <h2>The Game-Winning Moment</h2>
            <p>With the game tied at 128 in overtime, LeBron took matters into his own hands. Driving past Draymond Green, he finished with a signature fadeaway jumper that gave the Lakers a two-point lead with 1.4 seconds remaining.</p>

            <p>The Warriors' final attempt fell short as Klay Thompson's buzzer-beater rimmed out, sealing a vital win for the Lakers in their push for playoff seeding.</p>

            <h2>Playoff Implications</h2>
            <p>This victory moves the Lakers up to the 5th seed in the Western Conference, while the Warriors now face a tougher path with only four games left in the regular season.</p>

